ning new light on the CIA-KGB spy wars, he invites deeper thinking about the history of espionage and its implications for the intelligence community today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEspionage, AmericanxSoviet Union. 0aEspionage, AmericanzSoviet Union. 0aIntelligence officersxBiographyxSoviet Union. 0aIntelligence officersxBiographyxUnited States. 0aIntelligence officerszSoviet UnionvBiography. 0aIntelligence officerszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aIntelligence servicexHistoryxSoviet Union. 0aIntelligence servicezSoviet UnionxHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013478040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300134780423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300134780/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles